.TH SIGNAL 3F
.SH NAME
signal \- specify Fortran action on receipt of a system signal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "integer i"
.B "external integer intfnc"
.P
.B "call signal(i, intfnc)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Signal\^
allows a process to specify a function to be invoked upon receipt
of a specific signal. The first argument specifies which fault or
exception, the second argument the function to be invoked.
.SH SEE ALSO
kill(2), signal(2).
